                            <comment id="12948876" author="davsclaus" created="Sun, 21 Sep 2008 07:26:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for reporting this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Route is hardly used in Camel as we use the model RoutesType to build the route paths.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12948894" author="davsclaus" created="Sun, 21 Sep 2008 10:14:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hardly used by end-users I mean. End-users usually add the routing using a route builder that uses the models. But I think I got it fixed now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12948887" author="davsclaus" created="Sun, 21 Sep 2008 11:35:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Currently Camel doesn&apos;t properly support removing existing routes and adding new dynamically. This is scheduled for Camel 2.x.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You should use the camelContext.addRoutes(routeList) to add you new routes to an existing context.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At present time we can not add a fix for this as it will break to much at current time.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12948850" author="davsclaus" created="Sun, 21 Sep 2008 12:08:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I will cleanup the unused routes in RouteBuilder and add a throws UnsupportedOperationException for setRoutes in CamelContext.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12948901" author="davsclaus" created="Sun, 21 Sep 2008 17:08:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Changing to fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12948832" author="davsclaus" created="Sun, 21 Sep 2008 17:09:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Notice that you should use addRoutes. setRoutes is not possible until Camel 2.x&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12947543" author="davsclaus" created="Mon, 16 Feb 2009 05:51:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing all 1.5.0 issues&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
